caption: Choice Market is a cozy eatery on Lafayette and Grand Ave in Brooklyn.  I had the turkey burger with fries. Also, I has a chocolate peanut butter cookie. The burger was epic with a layer of sliced cucumber or pickles?, avocado, lettuce, onion, tomato and mayo. The burger was seasoned well and not dry. I added the accompanying chipotle sauce and it added another level of taste!The fries were good. I do prefer them well done but these were good just the same. I had the garlic fries on the first visit. Yum!  The cookie was rich and crumbly- the way I like them. Choice Market has other items on their menu which I am sure are just as delish and savory as the turkey burger. So.... go ahead and order a bunch of tasty grub from Choice Market. You will be pleasantly satisfied.
I love this place...
Great food and friendly staff.  Lovely place

I rarely post Google reviews, but I feel compelled to do so in this case in order to show appreciation for the lovely team of people at Choice Market. I had an unfortunate experience today whereby the paper bag containing my food order ripped a few blocks from the shop and spilled its contents on the street. I went back to Choice with the torn bag and remaining scarps of food to explain what happened, and they really couldn't have handled the situation more gracefully. Thank you again for your kindness; it was deeply felt. What's more, the food was absolutely delicious (boeuf bourguignon with mashed potatoes, kale, and mushrooms).
Great place to eat. Food was fresh fast and delicious.

I think they are a little too ambitious and have way too much on their menu, leaving them not really to excel in any items. "Jack of all trades, master of none" type of situation.

Lunch and dinner staple for us! We love the impossible burger and fries. Their salads are nice and hearty. I recently tried the prosciutto sandwich and I think I’m in love with a sandwich. Perfect blend of prosciutto, arugula, and mozzarella seasoned with pesto and arugula. Can’t wait to try their chicken salad sandwich and the chicken panini.  Great portion sizes and price. The staff is always incredibly friendly when we pop in.

This place has a vast menu, which changes depending on the menu's source. Once you find something you love, you'll be back for more! Good sandwiches. The chocolate chip walnut cookie is my favorite cookie, and is usually pretty good. Today I got the chocolate + chocolate cookie, and found it stale or at least unappetizing/inedible to me. But overall definitely love and appreciate this place, which continues to be one of the best spots in the neighborhood. Also don't look over their egg sandwiches, which I think are available all day. Finally, I've had only positive interactions with staff, who I find to be helpful, understanding, and efficient!  UPDATE: I mentioned yesterday’s stale cookie today when I ordered/picked up an egg sandwich, and it was much better!
turkey burger was dry the burger bun was over roasted . not what I'm use to

I absolutely luuuuuurve Choice Market!!!  I got into them while that franchised coffee shop opposite was closed due to the pandemic. I apologize Choice. I didn't know any better. Will fix this with more visits.  I've been to them about five six times during the height of covid and was afraid to contaminate my phone by taking pics. Must rectify this.  The staff is amazing!!!! During the pandemic management and staff thanked each customer individually. Not just with the regular old "thanks youssss" but with so much apprecilove! Like the Grammies and shxt! I in return thanked her one day for her essential service but she threw it back at me "no, thank, YOU for taking the time to support us during this difficult period." Man I wanted to cry. What an emotional time we've been (are) in.  This "mum and pop" absolutely have my vote!  Their store is always immaculate and their food is yummy coffee so delicious!  Please support them.  The End.

I had their BLT and it absolutely blew me away. The sandwich is loaded with crispy bacons with just the right amount of moist, and the rosemary mayo went great with the bacon. Highly recommended! Didn't get to try their pastry, but they all look very good. I'll have to find time and come back again.  Tip: the place can get crowded and service can slow down significantly during lunch hour.
